# Setup_PrisonersDilemma_Live.gsl
#
# Sets up a live 2-player Prisoner's Dilemma session in the browser.
#
# Alice (the admin account) plays as Prisoner A in the main browser window.
# Bob   (mock account)      plays as Prisoner B — a second browser tab is
#                           opened automatically in browser mode.
#
# Usage:
#   python manage.py run_gsl Setup_PrisonersDilemma_Live.gsl \
#       --mode browser --headed --stay-open
#
# The --stay-open flag keeps the session alive after setup so that
# human players can take over and play interactively.
#
# To hand off Bob's tab to a second human player:
#   1. Copy the session URL from Bob's browser tab.
#   2. Open it in any browser and log in with the second player's account.
#   3. Assign the "Prisoner B" role from the lobby.
#
# SECURITY NOTE: plaintext password below.
# Replace with: Login admin $ADMIN_PASS display:"Alice"
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Session owner login ----------------------------------------------

Login admin pass1234 display:"Alice"


# --- Game selection ---------------------------------------------------

Select_Game prisoners-dilemma


# --- Create the session -----------------------------------------------

Create_Session name:"Live Prisoner's Dilemma"


# --- Second player (mock, in a second browser tab) --------------------

Add_Player mock display:"Bob"


# --- Role assignments -------------------------------------------------

Assign_role Alice "Prisoner A"
Assign_role Bob   "Prisoner B"


# --- Start the game ---------------------------------------------------

Start_game

# The session is now in the 'intro' phase.  Both players can read the
# rules before Prisoner A clicks "Start the Game" to begin Round 1.
#
# With --stay-open the portal will hold this session open until you
# close the browser or press Ctrl-C in the terminal.
